Expense Tracker API is a RESTful backend application built with Java and Spring Boot that helps users manage and track personal expenses. 
The system allows users to create, view, update, and delete expense records while organizing spending by category and date. 
The project follows a layered architecture using Controller, Service, and DAO components to separate responsibilities and improve maintainability.

Key Features

Add new expenses
View all expenses
Search expense by ID
Update expense information
Delete expenses
Categorize spending
Track expense amounts and dates

Technologies Used

Java
Spring Boot
REST API
Maven
UUID
In-Memory Data Storage (HashMap)
